<subSubSection pageId="14" pageNumber="15" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1437,866,972]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
Large dark flies, 
<quantity box="[352,440,866,892]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.8" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" unit="mm" value="18.0">18 mm</quantity>
. Proboscis narrowed apically, apex blunt (
<figureCitation box="[939,1027,866,892]" captionStart="FIGURES 24 – 28" captionStartId="10.[151,269,1976,2000]" captionTargetBox="[425,1189,474,1975]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[397,1189,474,1986]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 24 – 28. Heads. 24. C. amurensis. 25. Orthogonis sp. 26. C. sp. 27. C. caudatus. 28. C. caucasicus." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/175158/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
Fig. 
<number box="[994,1027,866,892]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" value="26.0">26</number>
</figureCitation>
). The proboscis is similar in shape to that of 
<taxonomicName authority="Meigen" authorityName="Meigen" box="[262,572,906,932]" class="Insecta" family="Asilidae" genus="Choerades" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fulva">
<emphasis box="[262,455,906,931]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Choerades fulva</emphasis>
(Meigen)
</taxonomicName>
, as recorded by 
<bibRefCitation author="Lehr" box="[760,904,906,932]" pageId="14" pageNumber="23" refString="Lehr, P. A. (1992) Small genera of robber flies of the subfamily Asilinae (Diptera, Asilidae), 2, Phylogeny. Zoologicheskiy Zhurnal, 6, 49 - 59." type="journal article" year="1992">
Lehr (
<number box="[831,895,906,932]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" value="1992.0">1992</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
. Additional South Korean specimens (including males) need to be collected and compared.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1437,1026,1732]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,655,1026,1052]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Description based on single female.</emphasis>
Head: Face black integument, white pollinose, long sliver hair. Mystax long, black, intermingled with a few short white hairs. Long, thick silver/white parafacial hair. Orbital hair long, black. Proboscis tapered to a blunt apex on apical 
<number box="[857,868,1106,1132]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number box="[880,895,1106,1132]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" value="3.0">3</number>
(fig 
<number box="[952,985,1106,1132]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" value="26.0">26</number>
). Long black postocular hair intermingled with some yellow hair. Ocellar tubercle with 
<number box="[759,774,1146,1172]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" value="2.0">2</number>
strong black dorsal bristles, 
<number box="[1125,1140,1146,1172]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" value="4.0">4</number>
shorter, finer bristles on margins. Antenna black with black hair; relative lengths of segments: 
<number box="[989,1004,1186,1212]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" value="3.0">3</number>
&gt; 
<number box="[1023,1040,1186,1212]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" value="2.0">2</number>
&gt; 
<number box="[1058,1069,1186,1212]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" value="1.0">1</number>
; postpedicel (segment 
<number box="[1342,1357,1186,1212]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" value="3.0">3</number>
) more than 
<number box="[208,223,1226,1252]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" value="3.0">3</number>
times the length of segment 
<number box="[558,573,1226,1252]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" value="1.0">1</number>
; postpedicel w a posterior apical pit. Facial bristles black, long, extending into mystax. Thorax: Scutum pale blue/black covered in dense short, fine yellow and black hair; yellow on medial and posterior surfaces. Postpronotal hair black. Chaetotaxy with: 
<number box="[1007,1022,1306,1332]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" value="2.0">2</number>
notopleural, 
<number box="[1178,1192,1306,1332]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" value="5.0">5</number>
supraalar, 
<number box="[1322,1336,1306,1332]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" value="4.0">4</number>
postalar bristles, all black. Long, fine black dorsocentral hair erect above shorter yellow hair. Discal scutellar hair, short, yellow, appressed, similar to that on posterior of scutum. Scutellar margin with long black bristles confined to outer margin. Lateral aspect of thorax black with gray pollen. Anepisternum with sparse, long, fine black hair; 
<number box="[287,302,1466,1492]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" value="2.0">2</number>
strong black posterior bristles. Katatergal bristles long, all black. Anatergite bare black. Legs: Entirely black with strong black bristles, white and black hair; hind tibia curved. Wings: Tinged black/brown, strongest surrounding veins. Abdomen: Black integument with short, sparse gold hair. Tergite 
<number box="[1278,1292,1546,1572]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" value="2.0">2</number>
with strong lateral gold hair and bristles. Tergites 
<number box="[607,651,1586,1612]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" value="5.5" valueMax="7.0" valueMin="4.0">4–7</number>
with stronger, medial gold hair; tergites 
<number box="[1143,1187,1586,1612]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" value="2.0" valueMax="3.0" valueMin="1.0">1–3</number>
without medial hair. Male: Unknown.
</paragraph>
